Reasoning: The paper deals with the study of extensions of polytopes of combinatorial optimization problems, which is a topic in computational geometry and combinatorics. The specific problem studied is the Minimum Spanning Tree problem, which is a classic problem in graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also mentions the use of the fooling set method, which is a technique in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science, suggesting the sub-categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as additional possibilities.
